Incident: Passwd Found in Requested URL - Possible LFI Attack

Indicators:
Alert Trigger Reason : Passwd Found in Requested URL - Possible LFI Attack
Source IP: 106.55.45.162
Source port: 49028
Destination IP: 172.16.17.13
Destination Port: 443

Investigation:
Understanding why alert was triggered:
  URL Contains passwd

Traffic information:
SOURCE:
  After researching ip address using ARIN Whois/RDAP, The IP address is owned by TencentCloud, a cloud service provider located in Beijing.

DESTINATION:
  The destination is a webserver on the simulated SIEM.

PROTOCOL:
  The protocol being used: HTTPS

Findings:
  An attacker using a cloud service provider domain to attempt an LFI attack, they attempted to access a password file on the server.

  This user is not on the company network.

  After looking through logs the attacker did a classic LFI request. This traffic is malicous.

  Just to be sure, I analyzed the email logs to check if this was a scheduled test, it was not. Nothing like that was ever mentioned.

  The traffic flow is Internet -> Company network.

  After analyzing the logs, the attempts all resulted in response code 500, these requests didn't go through and sent back a server error.

Conclusion:
  True positive alert.

Response:
  Requests were unsuccessful. No further action required.
